Call the National Careers Service helpline for information and advice about jobs, careers and training if you’re 13 or older in England.

chunks.html_content:
You can also arrange for a National Careers Service adviser to call you - this will not cost you anything.

Contact the National Careers Service Exam Results Helpline for free advice if you’ve received exams results that were not as good as you were expecting.

The helpline is open from A level results day until a week after GCSE results day.
